  "body": "should fix: https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/issues/880#issuecomment-395369943\r\n\r\n### What is wrong?\r\n\r\nhttps://www.cs.bu.edu/%7Egoldbe/projects/eclipseEth\r\n\r\nWe should add protection against eclipse attacks.\r\n\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\nTwo things:\r\n\r\n- The peer pool should be configurable for how many connections may be made to the same IP address.  I think a default of `2` should be acceptable here.\r\n- The peer pool should require that a certain percentage of peer connections be outgoing (dial out).  Lets require `1/4` of our peer connections to be outbound (with a strict lower bound of `1` if the peer pool max peers is `>2` and no lower bound if `max_peers == 1`).",
