    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "As I believe was suggested in the gitter channel by @gsalgado \r\n\r\n- Add a new method `PeerPool.is_valid_connection_candidate(node)` which takes a `kademlia.Node` instance and returns `True` or `False` depending on whether the node should be considered.  Within this method you can implement the check for whether we have an existing peer with the same IP address.\r\n- In `Server._receive_handshake()` use this new method to either reject the handshake if it returns `False`.\r\n- In `PeerPool.get_nodes_to_connect()` use this new method to filter the returned nodes.",
